3 Sec. 2.3. Chapter 209 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
4 thereto a new section to read as follows:
5 1. On or before September 30 of each year, programming
6 staff at each institution or facility of the Department shall provide
7 to offenders who wish to receive it information on the importance
8 and benefits of financial planning and completing the Free
9 Application for Federal Student Aid. The information must
10 include, without limitation:
11 (a) An explanation that financial aid may be used to attend an
12 online, trade or vocational school; and
13 (b) A description of the types of financial aid available to
14 persons who are lawfully present in the United States under any
15 federal law, regulation, policy or program administered by a
16 federal agency or department.
17 2. The information described in subsection 1 must be
18 provided:
19 (a) During the year immediately preceding the date on which
20 an offender is projected to be released from the custody of the
21 Department; or
22 (b) Upon the setting of a parole eligibility date, as part of the
23 pre-release planning process.
24 3. The programming staff described in subsection 1 shall
25 offer assistance with completing the Free Application for Federal
26 Student Aid to offenders who wish to receive it. Such assistance
27 may be provided on an ongoing basis and must include:
28 (a) At least one designated Free Application for Federal
29 Student Aid event during the first week of October; and
30 (b) At least one designated Free Application for Federal
31 Student Aid event during the last week of February.
32 4. The information and assistance described in subsections 1
33 and 3 may be provided in person or through virtual means and
34 may be integrated into other programs, classes, institutional
35 policies or public postings within an institution or facility.
36 5. The programming staff described in subsection 1 shall, as
37 appropriate:
38 (a) Provide offenders with guidance on employment
39 opportunities that may be available following release;
40 (b) Identify circumstances in which a recommendation to an
41 offender to apply for financial aid is appropriate;
