1 (c) Assist offenders in obtaining documentation necessary to
2 complete a Free Application for Federal Student Aid;
3 (d) Permit eligible visitors, including family members, to
4 attend Free Application for Federal Student Aid events and to
5 bring required documents or materials on behalf of the offender;
6 (e) Provide offenders with training on managing finances
7 while in the custody of the Department and after release; and
8 (f) Coordinate with institutions of higher education, public
9 libraries and other community organizations to support Free
10 Application for Federal Student Aid, offer offenders informational
11 sessions, assist offenders with registration and facilitate offenders’
12 access to educational and vocational opportunities.
13 6. The Department and staff of the Department shall not use
14 the decision of an offender to apply for financial aid or to
15 participate in any activity described in this section as a basis to
16 impose a sanction or grant a privilege, incentive or other benefit.
17 7. Each institution and facility of the Department shall, on or
18 before January 31 of each year, submit to the Department a report
19 concerning the implementation and outcomes of the services
20 provided pursuant to this section. The Department shall compile
21 and summarize such reports and submit the summary to the Joint
22 Interim Standing Committee on the Judiciary in odd-numbered
23 years.
24 8. Any program offered by the Department on July 1, 2025,
25 that provides substantially the same information, assistance and
26 services described in subsections 1 to 5, inclusive, shall be deemed
27 to satisfy the requirements of this section, so long as the
28 Department continues to offer the program without substantial
29 interruption.
30 9. As used in this section, “programming staff” means staff
31 designated to provide programming services as part of a reentry
32 program at an institution or facility, or other appropriate staff if
33 such personnel are not designated.
34 Sec. 2.7. The provisions of subsection 1 of NRS 218D.380 do
35 not apply to any provision of this act which adds or revises a
36 requirement to submit a report to the Legislature.
37 Sec. 3. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
